<div id="review_3105899525" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3105899525" />
    <a title="Michelle" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/5858203-michelle"><img alt="Michelle" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1520844755p2/5858203.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3105899525?book_show_action=true">Sep 01, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Michelle" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Michelle" href="/user/show/5858203-michelle">Michelle</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/10442269-if-there-be-thorns">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3105899525" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3943240804224716843">I saw a quote this week where VC Andrews had said if a book didn&apos;t hold her interest she was quick to DNF it and how she made sure her books held the readers attention and I have to say she does achieve this. I&apos;d describe her writing style as frantic, you are literally in a whirlwind of family drama for 400 pages and you can&apos;t look away. <br/><br/>Book three in a series and you really do need to read the previous two to have any idea what&apos;s going on here, without the back story this will read way weirder </span>
  <span id="freeText3943240804224716843" style="display:none">I saw a quote this week where VC Andrews had said if a book didn't hold her interest she was quick to DNF it and how she made sure her books held the readers attention and I have to say she does achieve this. I'd describe her writing style as frantic, you are literally in a whirlwind of family drama for 400 pages and you can't look away. <br /><br />Book three in a series and you really do need to read the previous two to have any idea what's going on here, without the back story this will read way weirder than the weird its meant to be. <br /><br />As per the previous two books this one is filled with every drama and trope possible and its very chaotic but i'm enjoying the craziness, its easy reading that makes you feel like you're on acid and definitely takes you away from real life.</span>
