        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1140008771" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2769436324616700157">This novel is the third book in a series. You could read this one as a stand alone but reading the previous ones would be beneficial. In this one it has been several years for Cathy and her family. Then one day a mysterious older woman moves in next door and we all know this will not be good news. This story is told through Cathy&apos;s children Jory and Bart.<br/><br/>The only positive aspect of this novel was Jory and Bart&apos;s viewpoint. I liked it as it provided a fresh take on events. The negative about usin</span>
  <span id="freeText2769436324616700157" style="display:none">This novel is the third book in a series. You could read this one as a stand alone but reading the previous ones would be beneficial. In this one it has been several years for Cathy and her family. Then one day a mysterious older woman moves in next door and we all know this will not be good news. This story is told through Cathy's children Jory and Bart.<br /><br />The only positive aspect of this novel was Jory and Bart's viewpoint. I liked it as it provided a fresh take on events. The negative about using that way to tell a story is if you do not like one of the characters and I did not like Bart. He was meant to be written as evil but he came across as petulant and his tantrums which were meant to convey his nastiness actually made me shake my head at the absurdity of them. In my opinion the author did not get in the head of a child.<br /><br />I also thought the plot points were too circumstantial. Bart's progression was way out there and I did not enjoy his story at all. If you are asking why two stars instead of one is I did enjoy the theme of redemption in this book. It shows that parents are not perfect but they want to be forgiven by their children. I think the author had the right idea and if she conveyed it differently this could have been an enjoyable read.</span>
  <a data-text-id="2769436324616700157" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


